      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The big one of the day, which includes defending champion ANGRY SKIES, who again looks a key player. BLACK STORM (2) might be his biggest stumbling block for back-to-back Cups, coming off a nice win in the Albury Mile on Cup Day. That came after a Bendigo trial win, which proved he had bounced back from the Caulfield flop and, despite the wide draw, he'll be looking to race on speed, which would aid his prospects. ANGRY SKIES (5) only had 1kg more than last year, when he won on a plain run in BM78 grade at Caulfield, but comes into this off a fourth in the Bairnsdale Cup, which is probably superior form. WILD IMAGINATION (4) is a fascinating runner over from WA, but brings some good ratings with him and rarely runs poorly. GOLD BULLION (1) is another newcomer to Vic, previously trained by Waterhouse/Bott, and he looked to move well in a recent trial win. CHARTRES (6) needs to lift, but likes to race on-speed and draws to do so.",
